Privacy policy
This Privacy Policy governs the manner in which Scenic (“Administrator”) collects, uses, maintains and discloses information collected from users (each, a “User”) of the scenic.app website and scenicapp.space website (“Site”) and the Scenic mobile app (“Apps”). This privacy policy applies to the Site, App and all products and services offered by Scenic.
This Privacy Policy is incorporated as part of the
Scenic Terms of Use
(the ” Terms of Use ” or the ” Terms “). Your use of the Services is subject to the Terms of Use and this Privacy Policy and indicates your consent to them.
Any user wishing to register on the Site or in the Apps must first read and accept this Privacy Policy conditions. Any User who does not accept the content of this Privacy Policy must refrain from registering on the Site and for the App.
The data Users supply to the Administrator when they register, as well as all data supplied through the Site and the App, are stored in a database held in the name of and owned by the Administrator, who is responsible for the said database.
The Administrator collects and processes Users’ data in order to identify them as users of the Site and the App, and to allow them access to all services offered by the Site and the Apps.
Use of the Site and the App means that you expressly consent to having your personal data processed by the Administrator for the purpose of allowing the provision in full of the services that are the subject of the Scenic activity, and processing any requests you may wish to make, such as for example: complying with your request to include your personal data in our databases, enroll you as a registered user on our website, manage you as a client, or answer your request for information.
Use of the Site and the App means that you consent to the administrator sharing your de-identified activity data with 3rd party marketing and analytics companies for the purpose of continuous app improvement and measuring ad attribution. In the iOS App, Users are explicitly asked for consent with regard to sharing activity data across companies. If consent is not given, no activity data will be shared with 3rd party marketing and analytics companies.
Users, as the owners of their data, may exercise their rights to access, amend, correct, delete, and challenge the said data. To do this, you should
contact the Administrator
.
Users warrant that the personal data they supply when they register in order to access the App are accurate, truthful, and up to date, and they undertake to update them as necessary so that they always reflect their current situation.
By accepting this Privacy Policy, Users expressly authorize the Administrator to send them information concerning offers, activities, promotions, products, services, etc. (by e-mail) that the Administrator considers to be of interest to the User, both from Scenic and from third parties.
Users may object to receiving communications for commercial and/or promotional purposes at any time by
contacting the Administrator
.
Persons aged under 14 are not allowed to register and their information may not be used. If you are aged under 14, please do not try to register on the Site or the Apps, and do not supply us with any personal information. Any information that is found to belong to a person aged under 14 shall be deleted as quickly as possible. If you believe we may have information in our possession belonging to a person aged under 14, we would be grateful if you would inform us by
contacting the Administrator
.
If you wish to close your account and delete your profile for good, you can so through the App, or
contacting the Administrator
.
Users should bear in mind that if they close their account for good, they will lose all their profile information, along with everything associated with this (loss of contacts, photographs, etc.).
Hyperlinks featured on the application may redirect you to external websites. The administrator accepts no responsibility for the content of the said websites, or the information or services that may be offered on the said websites, which are offered for exclusively informative purposes, and under no circumstances shall this entail any relationship between Scenic and the owners of the said external websites or the owners of the sites where they are hosted.
Location based information
The Service collects your location to create a detailed location history of all of the journeys you have made while using the Service. The Service will use this information for the following purposes only:
to operate the Services and to improve and customize your experience with the Services;
to improve the experience of other users. The Service may use your route information to improve the accuracy of its mapping and navigation data;
to provide you with support and handle requests and complaints;
to send you updates, notices, announcements, and additional information related to the Services;
to create aggregated and/or anonymous data (where such data does not enable the identification of a specific user);
to conduct surveys and questionnaires;
to share your submissions with other users of the Services and to facilitate communication between you, the Service and other users;
to enforce the Terms of Use;
to contact you when Scenic believes it to be necessary;
to comply with any applicable law and assist law enforcement agencies under any applicable law, when Scenic has a good faith belief that Scenic’ cooperation with the law enforcement agencies is legally mandated or meets the applicable legal standards and procedures;
to prevent fraud, misappropriation, infringements, identity theft and other illegal activities and misuse of the Services;
to handle breakdowns and malfunctions;
to take any action in any case of dispute, or legal proceeding of any kind between you and the Service, or between you and other users or third parties with respect to, or in relation with the Service;
Use of cookies and hyperlinks
The Site may use cookies when a user is browsing through its pages. Cookies are only associated with the browser of a particular computer (an anonymous user), and are unable to provide the name or any other information about the user. By using cookies, Scenic is able to recognize the preferences selected by users in previous visits regarding the contents of the Site and can remember these preferences so you don’t have to select them again in subsequent visits. Please consult the instructions and manuals of your browser in order to obtain further information on how users can configure the receipt of cookies on their browser and prevent them from being installed on the hard drive of their computer. The installation of cookies sent from Scenic is not necessary in order to use the Site, although in this case it will be necessary for the user to make this selection each time he/she accesses the Site.
Changes to the data protection policy
The Administrator reserves the right to amend and/or change the security and data protection policy in order to adapt it to any legislative reforms or new caselaw, or to any innovations in the standard-form codes existing in this matter, or as a result of strategic corporate decisions, and for this purpose it shall be sufficient for any such amendment and/or change to be published in the Privacy Policy section of the www.scenic.app website, with immediate effect as from the date of publication.
However, at the discretion of Scenic, and without prejudice to the foregoing, additional notice of the changes and/or amendments may also be given by e-mail.
Contacting us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, the practices of this site, or your dealings with this site, please
contact the Administrator
.
